LIWAG.definition: 1. to put out of one’s thought, to banish.
LIWAG.eng_example: They were the ones who banished by sadness. 2. to distract, divert, amuse, cheer up.
LIWAG.ilok_example: Isuda ti nangiliwliwag ti ladingit ko.

LIWES.eng_example: It was he who took us around.

LIWLIW.definition: to do by a circuitous route, to do in a roundabout way.
LIWLIW.eng_example: Go there in a roundabout way.

LIWLIWA.definition: to console, comfort, solace, raise the spirit of.

LOKAL.definition: local, made in or originating from the locality.

LOTE.definition: a subdivision of a block in a town or city, a lot.

LUA.definition: to shed, or fill with, tears.

LUALO.definition: to pray, recite as a prayer.

LUANG.definition: loose and shaking as a jar or can half full of water.

LUAS.definition: to leave on a trip, to travel.
LUAS.eng_example: We will leave on a trip tomorrow.

LUBBO.eng_example: The boat on which they were riding sank.
LUBBO.ilok_example: Nalbo diay nagluganan da nga biray.

LUBBON.definition: to pair with as in riding, sleeping, etc.
to be paired with each other.

LUBBOT.definition: to pass through (a hole, an opening, etc.).
LUBBOT.eng_example: My head won’t pass through my dress.
LUBBOT.ilok_example: Saan nga lumbot daytoy ulok ti daytoy badok.

LUBBOT.definition: to put or pass (something) through (a hole, an opening, etc.).

LUBI.definition: to make a kind of sticky sweet made of DIPPIG bananas, DIKET rice, grated coconut meat and sugar; or of cassava root, grated coconut meat and sugar.
to make into this kind of sweet.

LUBNAK.definition: to wallow or play in a puddle.
to throw into or make fall in a puddle.

LUBO.definition: to cause to get stuck (in mud, debt, etc.).
to get stuck (in mud, debt, etc.).

LUDEK.definition: to be partially or not fully cooked: said of rice.

LUDON.definition: to put together without any order, to throw into a heap.

LUDONG.definition: n, a PURONG when more than a foot long.

LUGAD.ilok_example: Saan mo nga lugaden dayta poste.

LUGAN.definition: 1. vehicle, means of transportation. 2. load, passenger. 3. the taking of a vehicle.

LUGAR.definition: 1. place, spot, situation. 2. chance, opportunity, time.
to stay, put oneself in (a place).
to put, place (someone or something) (in a place).
to have the chance or time to do.

LUGAW.definition: to make rice gruel or porridge.

LUGAY.definition: to take off the hat to (someone).
LUGAY.eng_example: He does not want to take his hat off to the captain.
LUGAY.ilok_example: Dina kayat nga lugayan diay kapitan.

LUGI.definition: 1. to be shortchanged, to be cheated. 2. to suffer a loss, as in business, to lose in a business transaction.
LUGI.eng_example: I will lose if I give that to you for one peso.
LUGI.ilok_example: Malugiak no ited ko kenka dayta ti pisos.

LUGLUG.definition: to make muddy or mushy by agitating with the hands or feet.

LUGPI.definition: to cause to become crippled or lame, to cripple.

LUGUB.definition: to stay close to, huddle around.
LUGUB.ilok_example: Saan mo nga luguban dayta apoy.

LUK-AT.ilok_example: Saan mo nga luk-atan dayta baboy.

LUKAB.definition: to pry open, separate the two opposing sides of.
LUKAB.eng_example: He will pry open those oysters.

LUKAG.definition: to be awakened in one’s sleep.

LUKAS.definition: to pull up the lower part of one’s dress: said of women.

LUKIP.definition: to lift or raise slightly especially along the edge.
LUKIP.eng_example: He will lift that mat slightly along the edge.

LUKIP.definition: to open lightly, set ajar (as a door, window, etc.).

LUKKIAP.definition: to pry loose or off, to detach by prying.
to be pried loose or off, to be detached.

LUKMO.definition: a crustacean whose shell has been removed.

LUKOG.definition: to shuffle (the cards) such that one will eventually get the trump cards as the cards are dealt out: a form of cheating; to trump.

LUKONG.definition: to enclose (a note, check, money order, etc.) with (a letter).
LUKONG.ilok_example: Ilukong mo daytoy dita surat mo.

LUKONG.definition: to be enclosed with or inside.
LUKONG.eng_example: There is money enclosed with his letter.
LUKONG.ilok_example: Adda kuarta nga nailukong ditoy surat na.

LUKOT.eng_example: Let us roll up these mats on which we slept.
LUKOT.ilok_example: Lukuton tayo dagitoy ikamen nga nagturogan tayo.

LUKOT.definition: to be rolled inside or with.

LUKSAW.definition: to be disgusted or irritated with.

LULO.definition: to cause (a fruit) to become soft by handling, dropping, beating, etc.
to become soft through handling, dropping, beating, etc.

LULOK.definition: to loosen, slacken as a string.
LULOK.eng_example: Slacken the string of your kite.
LULOK.ilok_example: Lulukam dayta lubid ti ullaw mo.

LULUNAN.definition: fontanel, the soft, boneless area on top of the head of a baby.

LUMBA.definition: to compete in a race, to race with each other.

LUMLOM.definition: to push through or under, to force to go under or in.
to be pushed through, under, or in.

LUNAS.definition: to be worn out such that the surface becomes smooth (as a coin).

LUNES.ilok_example: Saan mo nga lunesen ta badom.

LUNG-AW.definition: to come out, rise out, emerge (as when drowning).
to be free from sickness, danger, misfortune, hardships, etc.

LUNGNGUOP.definition: to be suffocated, stifled, or smothered with heat, as in a dense crowd.

LUNGOG.definition: hollow, a small valley, a depression.

LUNGPOS.eng_example: Don’t spread water over that kitchen.
LUNGPOS.ilok_example: Saan mo nga lungposen dayta kusina ti danum.

LUNGSOT.definition: to cause to rot, putrefy, decompose.

LUNOD.definition: to curse, call or bring evil or injury down on, damn.
LUNOD.ilok_example: Saan mo nga ilunod dagiti naganak kenka.

LUOB.definition: to stay or live (in somebody’s house).
1. to stay or live with. 2. to stay or live with as commonlaw wife or husband.

LUPAK.definition: to cause to sink or get stuck, to cause to submerge or go beneath the surface of (mud), to sink.
LUPAK.eng_example: Don’t sink your shoes in the mud.
LUPAK.ilok_example: Saan mo nga ilupak ta sapatos mo dita pitak.

LUPES.definition: sterile, barren, unable to have offspring.

LUPINAY.definition: to sit down on one’s breech with the legs folded and drawn close to the body; to crouch.

LUPING.definition: drooping, fallen (as the ears of a dog, the crest of a cock).

LUPISAK.definition: crippled, unable to stand or walk.
to sit on the ground or floor.

LUPOS.definition: to cast off the slough, outer skin, or shell of.

LUPOY.definition: weak, feeble, as one who falls down easily.

LUPTAK.definition: to chap, crack open, fissure: said of the lips, tongue, skin, etc.

LUSI.definition: to expose (the glans penis) by pushing back the foreskin.
to be exposed: said of the glans penis.

LUSIT.definition: to crush by putting a heavy weight on.
to be crushed by a heavy weight.

LUSLOS.eng_example: My ring is slipping off (my finger).

LUSLOS.ilok_example: Saan mo nga iluslos toy paldak.

LUSOB.definition: the tubular, earthenware lining of a well, well casing.

LUSONG.definition: to insert, put in or on, fit in.
to be inserted, thrust in, put in; to fall into.
LUSONG.eng_example: Rose’s foot fell into a hole.
LUSONG.ilok_example: Nailusong diay saka ni Rosa idiay abut.

LUSSOK.definition: to puncture, pierce, perforate, bore a hole through.

LUSSOT.definition: to go through, shoot or break through, pierce.

LUSULUS.definition: 1. to resign from one’s position or office. 2. to withdraw from one’s candidacy for a position or office.
to resign from, withdraw from (a position, an office, etc.).

LUTTOK.definition: to crack open as an egg.
LUTTOK.eng_example: He will crack open that egg.

LUYA.eng_example: Rose is easily induced to cry.

LUYLUY.eng_example: His nasal mucus is flowing out.
